    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nInside `nvim-pack://confirm`, inspecting a commit via hover (using the diff) may not be adequate. For instance, the float may be too small for a proper inspection. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`gx` (above a commit hash) opens the commit inside github / codeberg / whatever.\n\nThere's precedent for tuning `gx` inside special buffers (i.e., help files).\n\nSince `vim.pack` uses LSP, maybe `documentLink` could be used in the implementation.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That's an interesting idea!\n\nThe problem here is that I don't think there is a universal way of handling this that is independent of plugin's source. I.e. `https://github.com/user/repo` has one way of linking to the commit, `https://other.com/` another, etc. Maybe hard coding most popular platforms might reasonable here, though.",
