            "body": "> That's an interesting idea!\n\nThanks! \n\n> The problem here is that I don't think there is a universal way of handling this that is independent of plugin's source.\n\nYeah, I was afraid of that. Heuristically, I thought about using `[remote]/commit/[hash]`. Maybe this could avoid the need for hardcoding, if it happens to match the \"common\" platforms?",
