            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> instead of popping up an ephemeral window, opening a navigable buffer then, like a ui2 pager\n\nTo me, that's an XY-solution :)\n\nOn a serious note, \"a ui2 pager\" for diffs does sound much more \"special-cased\" compared to using `documentLink`, which is already an LSP feature. I'd be more inclined to accept this suggestion if the built-in difftool supported such use case (at which point it could be opened on a new tab?). But even then, opening the link to a remote can be helpful (e.g., the commit might reference an issue or PR, etc).",
