        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> But even then, opening the link to a remote can be helpful\n\nTo clarify, I'm not debating that `gx` for git remotes could be useful (more prior art: [1](https://github.com/linrongbin16/gitlinker.nvim) [2](https://codeberg.org/trevorhauter/gitportal.nvim/)).\n\nBut independently of that, `K` could still be enhanced in some way. I don't necessarily want to leave the editor just to inspect the logs more comfortably, it's like circumventing the problem.\n\nWhat about exposing a general mechanism for promoting floating windows to regular ones or pagers?",
            "created_at": "2026-04-06T11:23:57Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38700#issuecomment-4191945843",
            "id": 4191945843,
